PN,36103
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F361A1774461962
OL,3,CArmed robber who was fought off by
OL,4,Cshopkeeper jailed
OL,6,FDet Con Joseph Albutt, of South
OL,7,FYorkshire Police, said: "This was a
OL,8,Fhorrific armed robbery which could
OL,9,Fhave resulted in serious injury to an
OL,10,Finnocent shopkeeper, who showed
OL,11,Fimmense bravery and quick-thinking in
OL,12,Fdefending the store and apprehending
OL,13,FCarter-Ashton.
OL,15,F"The ordeal he went through, however,
OL,16,Fis simply unacceptable. No retail
OL,17,Fworker deserves to be threatened,
OL,18,Fharassed, abused or assaulted in the
OL,19,Fworkplace and I can't imagine the fear
OL,20,Fhe must have felt when faced with
OL,21,FCarter-Ashton's violent behaviour."
OL,1,Woz5~k4{$z%~s1z5jw=hw1         G3/4
